## Common Incidents

### High Latency (p99 > {{ primary_sla_ms | default(500) }}ms)

1. Check Grafana dashboard for {{ service_name }}
2. Identify slow endpoints from the Latency Distribution panel
3. Check database query times:
   ```bash
   kubectl exec -it $(kubectl get pod -l app={{ service_name }} -o jsonpath='{.items[0].metadata.name}') -- curl -s localhost:{{ port | default('8000') }}/metrics | grep db_query
   ```
4. Check integration latency:
   ```bash
   kubectl exec -it $(kubectl get pod -l app={{ service_name }} -o jsonpath='{.items[0].metadata.name}') -- curl -s localhost:{{ port | default('8000') }}/metrics | grep client_request
   ```
5. If database: check RDS metrics in AWS console
{% for dep in integrations %}
6. If {{ dep.name }}: check {{ dep.name }} status page{% if dep.documentation_url %} ({{ dep.documentation_url }}){% endif %}

{% endfor %}

### High Error Rate (> 1%)

1. Check error logs:
   ```bash
   kubectl logs -l app={{ service_name }} --tail=100 | jq 'select(.level=="error")'
   ```
2. Identify error type from structured logs
3. If 500 + database error: check RDS connectivity
4. If 500 + integration timeout: check downstream service
5. If 422: client sending invalid data — check recent deployments of calling services

### Service Unreachable

1. Check pod status:
   ```bash
   kubectl get pods -l app={{ service_name }}
   ```
2. If CrashLoopBackOff:
   ```bash
   kubectl logs $(kubectl get pod -l app={{ service_name }} -o jsonpath='{.items[0].metadata.name}') --previous
   ```
3. If Pending: check node resources:
   ```bash
   kubectl describe pod $(kubectl get pod -l app={{ service_name }} -o jsonpath='{.items[0].metadata.name}')
   ```
4. If OOMKilled: increase memory limit in `k8s/deployment.yaml`

### Database Connection Failure

1. Check RDS status in AWS console
2. Check security group allows pod IPs
3. Check connection pool:
   ```bash
   kubectl exec -it $(kubectl get pod -l app={{ service_name }} -o jsonpath='{.items[0].metadata.name}') -- curl -s localhost:{{ port | default('8000') }}/metrics | grep pool
   ```
4. If pool exhausted: increase max connections in config

